<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3718] [DS] deactivate might not move component state to unsatisfied</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3718</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After deactivating, we check to see if the state changed before moving to unsatisfied:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if ( acm.state() == this )&lt;/p&gt;
            {
                acm.changeState( Unsatisfied.getInstance() );
            }


&lt;p&gt;But the state might have been moved from Active to Registered meanwhile, so deactivate would leave us in the Registered state.  Instead, check if the state is a satisfied state, and if so, move it to unsatisfied.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
